headline: FTC’s Case Against Drug Managers on Hold After Commissioners Fired
summary: The agency has paused its lawsuit against three pharmacy-benefit managers because no current commissioners can participate in the case.

headline: Trump’s Move to Dump FTC’s Democratic Members Leaves Insulin Case in Limbo
summary: The Federal Trade Commission’s lawsuit against three large pharmacy-benefit managers over insulin prices is on hold after President Trump fired two of the agency’s commissioners.
